# Technical Specification: Trauma-Informed Intake Schema for UnityPath Social Service Gateway

**Document ID:** MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-TRAUMA-SCHEMA-v1.0  
**Author:** Senior Technical Architect, Meridian Systems  
**Date:** [Current Date]  
**Project Phase:** Eligibility Engine Modernization (Phase 2)  
**Revision History:** Initial draft based on client requirements for self-reported barriers integration.  
**Scope:** This specification defines a trauma-informed intake schema extension to the existing UnityPath gateway. It enables applicants to optionally self-report barriers (e.g., housing instability, health concerns, domestic trauma) during digital intake. The schema supports prioritization logic for caseworkers and automated routing to resources such as emergency housing referrals or family support services. This builds on the current system handling ~3,400 applications/week across 5 borough zones, ensuring compatibility with existing eligibility engines.

The design adheres to trauma-informed principles by incorporating optional fields, non-mandatory disclosures, and user-friendly prompts (e.g., allowing "prefer not to answer" options). No policy opinions are included; this is an implementation-ready technical blueprint assuming client legal/oversight approval.

## 1. Data Model

The intake schema is defined as a JSON Schema extension to the existing applicant profile model. It introduces a new `barriers` object within the root `applicant` structure. This allows for modular integration without disrupting core eligibility data (e.g., income, household composition).

### JSON Schema Definition

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "Trauma-Informed Intake Schema",
  "description": "Extension for self-reported barriers in UnityPath intake process.",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "applicantId": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique identifier for the applicant (auto-generated by system)."
    },
    "submissionTimestamp": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "ISO 8601 timestamp of submission."
    },
    "barriers": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Optional self-reported barriers. All fields are nullable to support opt-out.",
      "properties": {
        "housingInstability": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "isExperiencing": {
              "type": "boolean",
              "description": "Flag indicating current housing instability."
            },
            "details": {
              "type": "string",
              "maxLength": 500,
              "description": "Optional free-text details (e.g., eviction risk, homelessness)."
            },
            "urgencyLevel": {
              "type": "string",
              "enum": ["low", "medium", "high", "preferNotToAnswer"],
              "description": "Self-assessed urgency for prioritization."
            }
          }
        },
        "healthConcerns": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "isExperiencing": {
              "type": "boolean",
              "description": "Flag indicating health-related barriers."
            },
            "details": {
              "type": "string",
              "maxLength": 500,
              "description": "Optional free-text details (e.g., chronic illness, mental health)."
            },
            "urgencyLevel": {
              "type": "string",
              "enum": ["low", "medium", "high", "preferNotToAnswer"],
              "description": "Self-assessed urgency."
            }
          }
        },
        "domesticTrauma": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "isExperiencing": {
              "type": "boolean",
              "description": "Flag indicating domestic trauma or violence."
            },
            "details": {
              "type": "string",
              "maxLength": 500,
              "description": "Optional free-text details (e.g., abuse history, safety concerns). Encrypted at rest."
            },
            "urgencyLevel": {
              "type": "string",
              "enum": ["low", "medium", "high", "preferNotToAnswer"],
              "description": "Self-assessed urgency."
            }
          }
        },
        "additionalBarriers": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "type": {
                "type": "string",
                "enum": ["foodInsecurity", "transportation", "employment", "other"],
                "description": "Category of additional barrier."
              },
              "details": {
                "type": "string",
                "maxLength": 500
              },
              "urgencyLevel": {
                "type": "string",
                "enum": ["low", "medium", "high", "preferNotToAnswer"]
              }
            }
          },
          "description": "Extensible array for other self-reported barriers."
        }
      },
      "additionalProperties": false
    },
    "routingPreferences": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "preferredResources": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": ["emergencyHousing", "healthServices", "domesticViolenceSupport", "familyCounseling", "other"]
          },
          "description": "Applicant-selected resources for routing."
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "required": ["applicantId", "submissionTimestamp"]
}
```

**Key Design Notes:**
- **Trauma Sensitivity:** All barrier fields are optional with "preferNotToAnswer" enums to avoid pressure. Details fields are free-text but limited in length for data efficiency.
- **Data Security:** Sensitive fields (e.g., `domesticTrauma.details`) must be encrypted at rest using AES-256 and access-controlled via role-based permissions (e.g., caseworkers only).
- **Extensibility:** The `additionalBarriers` array allows future expansions without schema changes.
- **Validation:** Server-side validation ensures no required fields force disclosure; urgency levels feed into prioritization algorithms (e.g., high urgency triggers immediate caseworker alerts).

## 2. API Contracts

The schema integrates via RESTful APIs extending the existing UnityPath intake endpoints. APIs use OAuth 2.0 for authentication and HTTPS for transport security.

### Endpoint: Submit Intake with Barriers
- **Method:** POST  
- **Path:** `/api/v1/intake/submit`  
- **Request Body:** JSON conforming to the schema above.  
- **Headers:**  
  - `Authorization: Bearer [token]` (applicant or proxy session token)  
  - `Content-Type: application/json`  
- **Response:**  
  - **200 OK:** `{ "status": "submitted", "applicationId": "string", "nextSteps": "array of recommended actions" }`  
  - **400 Bad Request:** Validation errors (e.g., invalid enum).  
  - **Example Response:**  
    ```json
    {
      "status": "submitted",
      "applicationId": "APP-123456",
      "nextSteps": ["Contact emergency housing hotline", "Schedule caseworker review"]

# Technical Specification: Stability Progress Tracker Extension for UnityPath Social Service Gateway

**Document ID:** MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-STABILITY-TRACKER-v1.0  
**Author:** Senior Technical Architect, Meridian Systems  
**Date:** [Current Date]  
**Project Phase:** Eligibility Engine Modernization (Phase 2)  
**Revision History:** Initial draft extending the trauma-informed intake schema (ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-TRAUMA-SCHEMA-v1.0). Incorporates requirements for tracking adherence to case-management goals and computing a monthly Stability Score for staff dashboard display.  
**Scope:** This specification defines an extension to the UnityPath system for a Stability Progress Tracker. It measures applicant adherence to goals such as appointment attendance, referral follow-through, and document submission. A derived monthly Stability Score (0-100 scale) is computed and displayed on the staff dashboard to assist caseworkers in prioritizing cases amid limited agency capacity. The tracker integrates with existing applicant profiles and eligibility engines, ensuring data from ~3,400 weekly applications is leveraged. All computations are automated and auditable, with scores used for internal routing and reporting only.

This design assumes client-approved policies for data usage and scoring algorithms; it provides implementation-ready details without policy commentary.

## 1. Data Model

The Stability Progress Tracker extends the existing applicant schema with a new `stabilityProgress` object. This object captures raw tracking data and computed scores. Data is stored in a time-series format to support monthly aggregations. Integration occurs via a relational database (e.g., PostgreSQL) with foreign keys to `applicantId`.

### JSON Schema Extension

The following extends the root schema from the prior intake specification. Only new or modified sections are detailed here.

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "Stability Progress Tracker Extension",
  "description": "Extension for tracking adherence and computing Stability Score.",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "applicantId": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique identifier linking to applicant profile."
    },
    "stabilityProgress": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Tracks adherence metrics and derived scores.",
      "properties": {
        "trackingEvents": {
          "type": "array",
          "description": "Time-series events for adherence tracking.",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "eventType": {
                "type": "string",
                "enum": ["appointmentAttendance", "referralFollowThrough", "documentSubmission", "other"],
                "description": "Category of the event."
              },
              "eventDate": {
                "type": "string",
                "format": "date-time",
                "description": "ISO 8601 timestamp of the event."
              },
              "status": {
                "type": "string",
                "enum": ["completed", "missed", "pending", "notApplicable"],
                "description": "Outcome of the event."
              },
              "details": {
                "type": "string",
                "maxLength": 500,
                "description": "Optional notes (e.g., reason for miss)."
              }
            },
            "required": ["eventType", "eventDate", "status"]
          }
        },
        "monthlyScores": {
          "type": "array",
          "description": "Computed monthly Stability Scores.",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "month": {
                "type": "string",
                "format": "date",
                "description": "First day of the month (e.g., '2023-10-01')."
              },
              "score": {
                "type": "number",
                "minimum": 0,
                "maximum": 100,
                "description": "Stability Score (weighted average)."
              },
              "breakdown": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                  "appointmentAdherence": {
                    "type": "number",
                    "description": "Percentage (0-100) of attended appointments."
                  },
                  "referralAdherence": {
                    "type": "number",
                    "description": "Percentage (0-100) of followed-through referrals."
                  },
                  "documentAdherence": {
                    "type": "number",
                    "description": "Percentage (0-100) of submitted documents."
                  }
                }
              }
            },
            "required": ["month", "score"]
          }
        },
        "lastUpdated": {
          "type": "string",
          "format": "date-time",
          "description": "Timestamp of last data update or score computation."
        }
      },
      "required": ["trackingEvents", "monthlyScores"]
    }
  },
  "required": ["applicantId"]
}
```

**Key Design Notes:**
- **Scoring Algorithm:** Monthly Stability Score is a weighted average: (appointmentAdherence * 0.4) + (referralAdherence * 0.3) + (documentAdherence * 0.3). Percentages are calculated as (completed / total expected) * 100 for events in the month. Scores are recomputed daily via a scheduled job (e.g., cron job in the backend).
- **Data Sensitivity:** Events are access-controlled; only authorized caseworkers can view/edit. Audit logs track all updates.
- **Extensibility:** `eventType` enum includes "other" for future goal types.
- **Storage:** Use a time-series optimized table (e.g., TimescaleDB extension) for efficient querying of monthly aggregates.

## 2. API Contracts

APIs extend existing UnityPath endpoints for staff interactions. All endpoints require staff authentication (OAuth 2.0 with role-based scopes, e.g., `caseworker:read` and `caseworker:write`).

### Endpoint: Log Tracking Event
- **Method:** POST  
- **Path:** `/api/v1/stability/log-event`  
- **Request Body:** JSON object for a single tracking event (from schema above).  
- **Headers:**  
  - `Authorization: Bearer [staff-token]`  
  - `Content-Type: application/json`  
- **Response:**  
  - **201 Created:** `{ "status": "logged", "eventId": "string" }`  
  - **400 Bad Request:** Validation errors.  
  - **Example Request Body:**  
    ```json
    {
      "applicantId": "APP-123456",
      "eventType": "appointmentAttendance",
      "eventDate": "2023-10-15T14:00:00Z",
      "status": "completed",
      "details": "Attended housing consultation."
    }
    ```

### Endpoint: Retrieve Stability Progress
- **Method:** GET  
- **Path:** `/api/v1/stability/progress/{applicantId}`  
- **Query Parameters:**  
  - `month` (optional): Filter to specific month (e.g., '2023-10'). Defaults to current month.  
- **Headers:** `Authorization: Bearer [staff-token]`

# Technical Specification: Stability Score Integration into Benefits Disbursement API for UnityPath Social Service Gateway

**Document ID:** MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-STABILITY-DISBURSEMENT-v1.0  
**Author:** Senior Technical Architect, Meridian Systems  
**Date:** [Current Date]  
**Project Phase:** Eligibility Engine Modernization (Phase 2)  
**Revision History:** Initial draft extending the Stability Progress Tracker (ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-STABILITY-TRACKER-v1.0) and trauma-informed intake schema (ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-TRAUMA-SCHEMA-v1.0). Incorporates requirements for integrating monthly Stability Score into benefits disbursement logic. For applicants with scores below a configurable threshold, a portion of cash assistance is converted to restricted digital credits redeemable via approved vendors. This supports automated disbursement workflows, aligning with program goals for spending patterns during recovery.  
**Scope:** This extension modifies the benefits disbursement process to query the latest monthly Stability Score. It introduces digital credit allocation, vendor restrictions, and redemption tracking. Integration ensures compatibility with existing eligibility and intake systems, handling ~3,400 weekly applications. Thresholds, conversion portions, and vendor lists are configurable via admin interfaces, assuming client-defined policies.

This design provides implementation-ready specifications, assuming all policy aspects (e.g., threshold values, conversion rules) have been approved by client legal and oversight teams.

## 1. Data Model

The disbursement model extends the applicant schema with a new `benefitsDisbursement` object, incorporating Stability Score references and digital credit details. Data is stored in a secure, auditable database (e.g., PostgreSQL with encryption for financial data). Foreign keys link to `applicantId` and `monthlyScores` from the stability tracker.

### JSON Schema Extension

The following extends the root schema from prior specifications. Only new or modified sections are detailed.

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "Benefits Disbursement with Stability Integration",
  "description": "Extension for score-based disbursement adjustments.",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "applicantId": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique identifier linking to applicant profile and stability data."
    },
    "benefitsDisbursement": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Disbursement details, adjusted by Stability Score.",
      "properties": {
        "disbursementDate": {
          "type": "string",
          "format": "date-time",
          "description": "ISO 8601 timestamp of disbursement."
        },
        "totalAssistanceAmount": {
          "type": "number",
          "minimum": 0,
          "description": "Total approved cash assistance (in USD)."
        },
        "stabilityScoreReference": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "month": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "date"
            },
            "score": {
              "type": "number",
              "minimum": 0,
              "maximum": 100
            }
          },
          "description": "Reference to the latest monthly Stability Score used for adjustments."
        },
        "cashPortion": {
          "type": "number",
          "minimum": 0,
          "description": "Unrestricted cash amount disbursed."
        },
        "restrictedCredits": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "amount": {
              "type": "number",
              "minimum": 0,
              "description": "Amount converted to restricted digital credits."
            },
            "expirationDate": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "date",
              "description": "Date after which credits expire (e.g., end of month)."
            },
            "approvedVendors": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "Vendor IDs (e.g., 'VENDOR-001' for grocery chains)."
              },
              "description": "List of approved vendors for redemption."
            },
            "redemptionStatus": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                  "transactionId": {
                    "type": "string"
                  },
                  "amountRedeemed": {
                    "type": "number"
                  },
                  "vendorId": {
                    "type": "string"
                  },
                  "timestamp": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "format": "date-time"
                  }
                }
              },
              "description": "Log of credit redemptions."
            }
          }
        },
        "adjustmentReason": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "System-generated note (e.g., 'Score below threshold; 30% converted to credits')."
        }
      },
      "required": ["disbursementDate", "totalAssistanceAmount", "stabilityScoreReference", "cashPortion"]
    }
  },
  "required": ["applicantId"]
}
```

**Key Design Notes:**
- **Adjustment Logic:** If Stability Score < threshold (configurable, e.g., 70), convert a portion (configurable, e.g., 30%) of `totalAssistanceAmount` to `restrictedCredits.amount`. Remaining becomes `cashPortion`. Logic executed server-side during disbursement processing.
- **Vendor Management:** Approved vendors maintained in a separate configurable table (e.g., `vendors` entity with ID, name, category like "groceries" or "housing"). Credits are redeemable only via API calls from these vendors.
- **Security and Audit:** Financial data encrypted at rest (AES-256). All disbursements logged with immutable audit trails for compliance.
- **Extensibility:** Configuration for threshold and conversion percentage stored in a system config service (e.g., via environment variables or admin API).

## 2. API Contracts

APIs extend existing UnityPath disbursement endpoints. All require authentication (OAuth 2.0 with scopes like `benefits:disburse` for staff/system processes). Integration with payment gateways (e.g., ACH for cash, custom ledger for credits) is assumed.

### Endpoint: Process Disbursement
- **Method:** POST  
- **Path:** `/api/v1/benefits/disbursement/process`  
- **Request Body:** JSON with applicant ID and total assistance amount. System auto-queries Stability Score.  
  - **Example Request Body:**  
    ```json
    {
      "applicantId": "APP-123456",
      "totalAssistanceAmount": 500.00,
      "disbursementDate": "2023-10-20T00:00:00Z"
    }
    ```  
- **Headers:**  
  - `Authorization: Bearer [system-token]` (automated or staff-initiated)  
  - `Content-Type: application/json`  
- **Response:**  
  - **200 OK:** Full disbursement object from schema (including adjustments).  
  - **400 Bad Request:** If score unavailable or invalid data

# Technical Specification: Household Stability Protocol Integration for UnityPath Social Service Gateway

**Document ID:** MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-HOUSEHOLD-STABILITY-v1.0  
**Author:** Senior Technical Architect, Meridian Systems  
**Date:** [Current Date]  
**Project Phase:** Eligibility Engine Modernization (Phase 2)  
**Revision History:** Initial draft extending the Stability Progress Tracker (ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-STABILITY-TRACKER-v1.0), Stability Score disbursement integration (ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-STABILITY-DISBURSEMENT-v1.0), and trauma-informed intake schema (ref: MS-ARCH-DHS-INTAKE-2026-089-TRAUMA-SCHEMA-v1.0). Defines the Household Stability Protocol for automated escalation based on persistent low or non-improving Stability Scores over review cycles.  
**Scope:** This specification outlines the protocol logic, data extensions, and integrations for automatic triggering of home assessments and sharing of behavioral case summaries with the Child and Family Services (CFS) interface. Escalation occurs if an applicant's monthly Stability Score fails to improve (e.g., remains below a threshold or shows no net increase) over a configurable number of successive review cycles (e.g., 3 months). The system evaluates household environment against agency care standards via CFS integration. This builds on existing tracking and disbursement features, ensuring seamless automation within the ~3,400 weekly application volume. Protocol parameters (e.g., improvement thresholds, cycle count) are configurable via admin tools.

This design assumes all protocol rules, data sharing, and escalation criteria have been approved by client legal and oversight teams; it provides implementation-ready technical details without policy analysis.

## 1. Data Model

The Household Stability Protocol extends the applicant schema with a new `householdStability` object. This captures protocol status, escalation history, and summary data for sharing. Data is stored in a secure relational database (e.g., PostgreSQL) with foreign keys to `applicantId` and `monthlyScores` from the stability tracker. Behavioral summaries are generated on-demand from aggregated tracking events and barriers data.

### JSON Schema Extension

The following extends the root schema from prior specifications. Only new or modified sections are detailed.

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "Household Stability Protocol Extension",
  "description": "Extension for protocol escalation and CFS integration.",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "applicantId": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique identifier linking to applicant profile, stability data, and disbursement records."
    },
    "householdStability": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Protocol status and escalation details.",
      "properties": {
        "protocolStatus": {
          "type": "string",
          "enum": ["monitoring", "escalated", "assessmentScheduled", "assessmentCompleted", "resolved"],
          "description": "Current state of the protocol."
        },
        "reviewCycles": {
          "type": "array",
          "description": "History of review cycles for improvement checks.",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "cycleMonth": {
                "type": "string",
                "format": "date",
                "description": "Month of the cycle (e.g., '2023-10-01')."
              },
              "score": {
                "type": "number",
                "minimum": 0,
                "maximum": 100,
                "description": "Stability Score for the cycle."
              },
              "improvementDelta": {
                "type": "number",
                "description": "Change from previous cycle (positive for improvement)."
              }
            },
            "required": ["cycleMonth", "score"]
          }
        },
        "escalationTriggers": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "triggerDate": {
                "type": "string",
                "format": "date-time"
              },
              "reason": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "e.g., 'No improvement over 3 cycles; score < 50'."
              },
              "actionsTaken": {
                "type": "array",
                "items": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "enum": ["homeAssessmentTriggered", "summarySharedWithCFS"]
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "description": "Log of escalation events."
        },
        "behavioralCaseSummary": {
          "type": "object",
          "description": "Generated summary for CFS sharing (encrypted at rest).",
          "properties": {
            "summaryText": {
              "type": "string",
              "maxLength": 2000,
              "description": "Aggregated narrative from barriers, tracking events, and scores."
            },
            "keyMetrics": {
              "type": "object",
              "properties": {
                "averageScore": { "type": "number" },
                "missedAppointments": { "type": "integer" },
                "householdSize": { "type": "integer" },
                "reportedBarriers": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }
              }
            },
            "generatedTimestamp": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "date-time"
            }
          }
        },
        "assessmentDetails": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "scheduledDate": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" },
            "outcome": { "type": "string", "enum": ["meetsStandards", "needsIntervention", "pending"] },
            "notes": { "type": "string", "maxLength": 1000 }
          },
          "description": "Details of triggered home assessment."
        }
      },
      "required": ["protocolStatus", "reviewCycles"]
    }
  },
  "required": ["applicantId"]
}
```

**Key Design Notes:**
- **Escalation Logic:** A scheduled job (e.g., monthly cron) evaluates `monthlyScores`. Escalation triggers if score < threshold (configurable, e.g., 50) and improvementDelta <= minDelta (configurable, e.g., 0) over numCycles (configurable, e.g., 3). Upon trigger: update status to "escalated", generate summary, schedule assessment, and share via CFS API.
