**Scope:** This specification outlines the architecture for a post-discharge monitoring system to track medication adherence, symptom check-ins, appointment attendance, and care-team outreach. The system enables early detection of patient destabilization (e.g., via predefined risk thresholds) and supports clinician interventions. It integrates with existing hospital systems (4 systems) and outpatient partners (27 entities) for data exchange. All designs adhere to client-approved policies on data privacy (HIPAA-compliant), consent-based monitoring, and escalation protocols.

## 1. System Overview
The monitoring system is a cloud-based platform built on a microservices architecture, leveraging AWS (or equivalent client-approved cloud provider) for scalability. It includes:
- **Patient Mobile/Web App:** For self-reported data (e.g., symptom check-ins, medication logging).
- **Clinician Dashboard:** For real-time monitoring, alerts, and outreach tools.
- **Backend Services:** For data processing, analytics, and integrations.
- **Key Capabilities:**
  - Automated tracking of medication schedules with reminders and adherence logging.
  - Daily/weekly symptom check-ins via surveys or biometric integrations (e.g., wearables for mood proxies like heart rate variability).
  - Detection of missed appointments via calendar integrations.
  - Automated alerts and outreach workflows for care teams when destabilization indicators are detected (e.g., missed doses > 2 in a week, symptom scores > threshold).
- **Security and Compliance:** All data encrypted at rest/transit (AES-256). Role-based access control (RBAC) with audit logging. Patient consent required for monitoring activation.

